"><span data-text=\"Ἔλπιστε\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Ἔλπιστος\">ΕΛΠΙΣΤΕ</span></span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ΑΜΕΜΠΤΕ</span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"ἔζησεν\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ΕΖΗΣΕΝ</span><span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ΕΤΗ</span><span data-text=\"κδ\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"κδ\">ΚΔ</span><span data-text=\"μῆνες\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"μείς\">ΜΗΝΕΣ</span><br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"δ\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"δ\">Δ</span><span data-text=\"ἡμέρας\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"ἡμέρα\">ΗΜΕΡΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"δ\" data-n=\"75\" data-lemma=\"δ\">Δ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Κουίντε\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Κουίντος\">ΚΟΥΙΝΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"Πομπῆι\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Πομπήιος\">ΠΟΜΠΗΙ</span><span data-text=\"Ἔλπιστε\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Ἔλπιστος\">ΕΛΠΙΣΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ΑΜΕΜΠΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span><span data-text=\"ἔζησεν\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ΕΖΗΣΕΝ</span><span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ΕΤΗ</span><span data-text=\"κδ\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"κδ\">ΚΔ</span><span data-text=\"μῆνες\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"μείς\">ΜΗΝΕΣ</span><span data-text=\"δ\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"δ\">Δ</span><span data-text=\"ἡμέρας\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"ἡμέρα\">ΗΜΕΡΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"δ\" data-n=\"75\" data-lemma=\"δ\">Δ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003380_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003380_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003380.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003380-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003380_rightthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003380_rightthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003380_rightthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003380_rightthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text from autopsy (Prag 2013). The text reported by IG 14.45a was transcribed by Salvator Politi and sent to Mommsen in 1884, but it is clear that Politi either lacked good lighting, or experience, or both, since all the points marked as omitted or unclear are in fact perfectly legible.</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>Quintus Pompeius Elpistus, worthy and blameless, farewell! He lived 24 hours, 4 months, 4 days.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The context of discovery is described in NSA (1884), 163 but without explicit reference to this piece, only to ISic003338. The reading provided in IG 14.45a is clearly deficient, and the text is fully legible. The urn was previously on display in Room 3 of the old archaeological museum in Siracusa, recorded in the 1929 guide by Libertini. It is currently in storage in the Museo Archeologico Regionale P. Orsi, Siracusa.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li>  <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">45a</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Libertini 1929 125 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001872\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001872</a>  </li><li> Manganaro 1988 50 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Deeply cut lunate letters of somewhat varying height. Kappa has tall vertical, lower tail extends to the line; Pi has vertical strokes of equal length, some overlap by horizontal; Mu has extended serifs off the upper strokes; epsilon and sigma are lunate, the cross-bar of the epsilon sometimes very lightly cut and detached; alpha and delta have extended serifs on the upper strokes; there is a single comma-shaped interpunct in line 1 after the first letter.</p> Line 1  23-32  Line 2  19-25  Line 3  17-25  Line 4  15-23  Line 5  15-20  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
